The article announces various nominations and appointments made by President Donald J. Trump. These include Sean Cairncross of Minnesota to be the Chief Executive Officer of the Millennium Challenge Corporation, Tim Thomas of Kentucky to be the Federal Co-Chair of the Appalachian Regional Commission, Kevin Edward Moley of Virginia to be an Assistant Secretary of State (International Organizational Affairs), Andrew Gellert of New Jersey to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Chile, Leandro Rizzuto of Florida to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to Barbados, St. Kitts and Nevis, and Saint Lucia, James Lynn Woodworth of Arkansas to be Commissioner of Education Statistics, Department of Education, for the remainder of a six-year term, and Michelle Giuda of New York to be an Assistant Secretary of State (Public Affairs). The article provides a brief background on each nominee or appointee.